cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with runtime monitoring of properties expressed in LTL and its extension LDLf, which are both logics used in computer science.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses providing operational decision support to running business processes, which is a common concern in software engineering.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the syntax of propositional dynamic logic (PDL), which is a programming language used to express temporal logic.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses using logical services to check monitoring metaconstraints, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses translating LDLf formulas into nondeterministic automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory.
